<br>
Total - 41 cards.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">To start: Delia leads, to do what she does - hordes and hordes of vellups.<br>
<br>
Pull on the Vellup, not the shooting star - sorreah is coming up next, and he doesn&#39;t want to be restricted to that spell.<br>
<br>
There are a number of single creatures in the deck - these are so that, whatever you&#39;re facing, you&#39;re prepped.<br>
<br>
Facing a Cald direct damage deck?  Vellups -> Elder Vellup -> Warlum.  Warlum -> Arderial Guard Wings.  Be happy.<br>
<br>
Facing a gigantic creature first turn?  V -> EV -> Alaban.<br>
<br>
Facing a heavy spell deck?  V->EV->Lovian<br>
<br>
Facing core?  V->EV->Yarothis.  And the Abwyn&#39;s Quill + Yarothis gives you a 6e recurring shockwave.<br>
<br>
If nothing is really needed, just use the Elder Vellups to set up Ora and Sorreah with the Xyx madness.<br>
<br>
Once Delia finally dies, Sorreah comes up.<br>
<br>
Sorreah gets a Dream, and 2 spells.  Usually, this will be a Cataclysm and something else.<br>
<br>
A Xyx + Sorreah&#39;s Dream + Cataclysm usually equals magi death (all cards gone, and 8 damage to the magi).<br>
<br>
It&#39;s risky, but can be fun.  Other than that, use the Rayalon to get your SD&#39;s and CoT&#39;s back, and play with Xyxes for fun.<br>
<br>
Once Sorreah goes, Ora comes in, and kills.  You should have a Xyx flood going quite well by Ora.  Use it.<br>
<br>
The Orothean Flyer is in the deck just for her as well - Summon it first turn, first, if you have it.  You pay 5, get 6 on it.  If it lives, more fun.  If not, it&#39;s still free energy.<br>
<br>
Blow up Xyx elders, grow your minors, pop the magi, and go go go!<br>
